The paper proposes a deep neural network module for human activity recognition, which involves modeling long-term temporal importance and determining the activity relevance of different temporal segments in a video. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed module involves a self-attention mechanism, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (NLP) and may suggest a connection to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with video data, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a learnable and differentiable module, which suggests a connection to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
